<h2 id="s9">9. Google Sheets Sync — Smart Diff Strategy</h2>

<h3>9.1 Why Not Delete-and-Rewrite?</h3>
<p>The original approach deleted all existing rows for a trip and re-appended fresh ones. Problems:</p>
<ul>
<li>Wasteful for 50 entries when only 1 is new</li>
<li>Risk of data loss during network interruption mid-delete</li>
<li>Breaks downstream formulas/charts that reference specific rows</li>
<li>Scales poorly — O(n) deletes + O(n) appends on every sync</li>
</ul>

<h3>9.2 Smart Diff Algorithm</h3>
<p>The doPost() function now uses positional comparison:</p>
<pre><code>// For each incoming row at position j:
if (j < existingRows.length) {
  // Compare with existing row at same position
  if (match) → skip       // Most common: 95% of rows
  if (!match) → update     // Rare: user edited an old entry
} else {
  → append                  // New entries at the end
}

// If notepad has fewer entries than sheet:
for (j = existingRows.length - 1; j >= incomingRows.length; j--) {
  → delete from bottom up   // Rare: user removed entries
}</code></pre>

<h3>9.3 Comparison Fields</h3>
<p>Six fields are compared per row: Date, Item, Amount, Currency, Method, Type. Trip name is used as the grouping key but not compared (it's the filter).</p>

<h3>9.4 Sync Timing</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Trigger</th><th>What Happens</th><th>Scope</th></tr>
<tr><td>Auto-push (2s debounce)</td><td>POST all parsed rows + raw text</td><td>Active trip only</td></tr>
<tr><td>Manual sync (refresh button)</td><td>POST active trip → GET latest 2 trips</td><td>Current + 1 previous</td></tr>
<tr><td>No URL configured</td><td>Button spins for 0.6s (visual feedback)</td><td>N/A</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>9.5 Notes Tab</h3>
<p>Raw notepad text is stored in the Notes tab (one row per trip). This is the source of truth for cross-device sync — when pulling, the raw text is used to recreate trips locally. The Expenses tab is the structured data layer for analysis.</p>

